Makueni woman representative Rose Museo yesterday urged residents to stop gender-based violence.Speaking when touring the county, she urged husbands to resolve marital differences in a peaceful manner."My office will work with Fida to help put an end to such kind of unethical behavior where husbands attack their wives and at times wives attack their husbands too," Museo said.He urged the National Government to set up centers within the county's where residents can get can help as a result of domestic violence.